<br>
<br>
You're farming no matter how you try to sugar coat it or hide behind the &quot;betterment of your guild&quot; line, that's what you're doing.  You farmed ToV for your Skyshrine/Kael armor and now you farm the North wing.  Don't even make me laugh by saying most of those dragons are so much more difficult to kill than a Kunark dragon.  More hit points does not automatically equate to more difficulty in slaying.  Clearing to them is a bigger pain than anything.  Most of the &quot;true dragons&quot; are perma rooted, so they can be debuffed (if they aren't unslowable) them mem blurred before the main assist engages.  Being perma rooted also equals automatic double damage for any trueshot using ranger.  They don't even fear.  I can tell you right now from firsthand experience, you don't need more than thirty people to kill anything there, except perhaps Vyemm and the Ring of Vulak event.  Armor farming for Skyshrine or Kael can be done with six.  Defensive warriors are not the only melee class that can tank flurry drakes.  <br>
<br>
and<br>
<br>
&quot;sorry I find that completely different from taking an AA skill (that doesn't even cost that much to get mind you) and using it to farm now trivialized dragons. Mid teir guilds are at a total disadvantage to compete with this small group of the population that doesnt even NEED these mobs.&quot;<br>
<br>
Need is a highly subjective term in a game.  Technically no warrior NEEDS NToV armor and weapons at this point in the game.  You/your guild WANT those items so different monsters are a little easier (trivial) to kill.  You obviously don't play a wizard as a primary character so you're really not expected to know the intricacies and relative difficulty of leveling one to 60 and accumulation of AA points and without the benefit of having a pre-established alternate character to twink it.  So as far as I'm concerned, your claims that manaburn is an easy to obtain skill for wizards is going to hold as much weight and credibility to me as the incessant  comments I hear of how quickly and easily archery mastery III or endless quiver are to obtain.  And that equals nothing.  People have different priorities and for some, accumulation of AXP points in this game isn't a high one.  For others, they really may not care to obtain an ability that will be of little to no use to them on a day to day basis so some flashy useable only once an hour ability is not going to be a skill they immediately decide to pick up.<br>
<br>
Trivial is also a subjective term.  If &quot;all&quot; a mid tier guild needs to kill a Kunark dragon is a puller then why can't they beat a manaburn team if that guild is there first.  I remember one Gorenaire raid where a ranger kited Gorenaire around while the rest of the raid arrived and buffed then pulled her in for the kill.  I guess mid-tier guilds are too good for that nowadays though and all pullers must be monks or bards.<br>
<br>
All this precious mid-tier content does prepare mid-level guilds for the high end game.  They learn that if they want to get a spawn they better get there first, which means learn to mobilize quicker or prepare in advance.  No high end guild is going to sit by and wait.  I'd like to see a manaburn team drop Wuoshi or the Va'Dyn so easily since they can steal all mid level content with impunity.<br>
<br>
