<br>
Warriors are the most expensive class to equip and do need to constantly upgrade.  Believe it or not, because we are in groups - I generally cant make the pp you speak of.  I have made 70k now in 4 months.  What have I sold ? Cobalt Helm(10k-bought for 20), Cobalt Bracer(20k-bought for 25k) - because both these were replaced and Silver Chitin Bracer(7k-bought for 10k) oh and in all this time, I have won one item (Silver shiverback belt-looted) - 20k.  The only thing I got left to sell is my cobalt BP when I get my SS BP.  <br>
<br>
So when you look at it, I have actually made 2k.<br>
<br>
And yes, I am looking for 250k to buy myself an SoD and going for Willsapper as well.  But in terms of gaining all of this equipment, as you well know I have worked my ass off for it and got little in return.  <br>
<br>
Being stuck in CT for 2 days over the weekend, I got nada which happens. But we got 4 pairs of FT3 boots which went to the casters because I am only prepared to be in groups who do NBG.  <br>
<br>
Finding caster stuff is just as easy as finding tank stuff, but it is entirely dependent on where you hunt. <br>
<br>
If you want to talk about pp generation, get a few people to go down to SG and farm the hell out of it.  You could easily end up with 20k a piece per night through gems <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub54.ezboard.com/urhesolooshun.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rhes Olooshun</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master of Dice</span><br>  Posts: 89<br> <font color=#00CCFF>(7/30/02 8:13:50 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub54.ezboard.com/fquelliousquaterstherebirthfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=417.topic&index=175>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Something I hoped never to see</span><hr size=1> Never thought I would see a post where Quas actually makes himself look uninformed, but I have now.<br>
<br>
I can tell you for a fact that it is a helluva lot more expensive to equip a TOP end warrior, than it is to equip a TOP end Wizard.  I can agree that you can easily twink a warrior to 50 for under 10k in items, but after that, any upgrades that are not no drop or questable cost an arm and a leg.  Also, I can submit to you that I can twink a wizard in comparable quality caster armor for easily 1/2 - 2/3 what it costs to twink a warrior.<br>
<br>
The top end warrior, barring quest armor, has several slots he can fill, Earrings/rings/belt/cloak/neck/face/range, for whatever stats he needs, HP/AC being the top two, and for any of the droppable things that are out there that have even decent stats in the HP/AC area, you are gonna pay thru the nose.  Simple economics, there are probably twice the warriors on Quellious in the level 55-60 range that there are Wizards, hence the demand on items is higher, which drives up prices.<br>
<br>
Check out my sig.  The droppable gear on me if I were to try and sell it would fetch 250k without even any effort.  The two earrings are 70-80k each, CoF another 70-80k, the Rubicite Belt is easily 80k, and if I really wanted to be stingy, I could probably get 100k+, and my weapons are the worst part of my armor, Frosty you can get for under 15k now, and the crafted velium is 10k or less as well as a Guard Capt's Mallet. <br>
<br>
Any upgrade that is droppable for me is gonna cast me plenty to buy.  PERIOD.<br>
<br>
Your argument about twinking a warrior to 50 holds no water in this discussion, as we are not talking about twinking, but about making cash to equip your main character.  <br>
<br>
I have a 52 wizzie myself, and he has staff of the wheel, which is the only no drop item on him, his intelligence is over 225, and the total cost value of the items on him if I were to purchase them today would be no more than 12-15k max.  And to top it off, I have met some 60 wizards that have compareable gear.<br>
<br>
Quas said<br>
<br>
